ny new optional zones there would be a NPC called "Al'Kabor's Taskmaster" who would be in charge of building the spires.  He would give the following quest:<br><br>You say, "Hail Al'Kabor's Taskmaster"<br>Al'Kabor's Taskmaster glances at you.<br>Al'Kabor's Taskmaster says, "I'm busy with the good work. Many [exciting things] will be happening [here] soon!"<br>You say, "What exciting things?"<br>Al'Kabor's Taskmaster says, "It is wonderous!  The master has perfected the [art] of building portals!  Soon we will be reclaiming the former glory of our order!"<br>You say, "What art?"<br>Al'Kabor's Taskmaster stares at you in disbelief.<br>Al'Kabor's Taskmaster says, "As if I would share the secrets with someone who does not understand the wizardly ways!"<br>You say, "I understand wizardly ways!"<br>Al'Kabor's Taskmaster says, "Then where is your proof?"<br>You say, "What proof?"<br>Al"kabor's Taskmaster says, "The proof you joined the order of course!"<br>You say, "I wish to join the order"<br>Al'Kabor's Taskmaster says, "Ah, only a great wizard may join the order.  Ask one of the masters about joining."<br><br>In Neriak and in Freeport in the Arcane Academy rarely a level 70 wizard will spawn named Al'trar the sorcerer.<br><br>You say, "Hail Al'trar the sorcerer"<br>Al'trar the sorcerer says, "Greetings lesser mortal"<br>You say, "I wish to join the order"<br>Al'trar the sorcerer scoffs at you.<br>Al'trar the sorcerer bows mockingly at you.<br>Al'trar the sorcerer says, "You may join the order, of course.  You merely must explain these pages to me."<br>Your faction with the order of Al'Kabor has gotten worse!<br>(You start indifferent, this hit moves you to dubious, you must be indifferent to talk to Al'trar)<br>You recieve: Incantations of Al'Kabor<br>Incantations of Al'Kabor must be combined by a wizard with 250 research skill along with a parchment and ink.<br>You succeed in creating something new!<br>Wizard_quester has created a Translation of Al'Kabor!<br>(You get back Incatations and Translation)<br>(You give the translation to Al'trar)<br><br>Al'trar the sorcerer blinks in surprise!<br>Al'trar the sorcerer says, "You understand much wizard.  Join us and help us build the portals to the unknown!"<br>Your faction with the order of Al'Kabor has gotten better!<br>You have gained experience!<br>You recieve a badge of ordination. (range int +10, all saves 40, focus (cast time 20%))<br>(You are now ally faction)<br><br>You say, "How can I help build the portals?"<br>Al'trar the sorcerer says, "Didn't you read what you wrote?"<br>You succeed in creating something new!<br>Wizard_quester has created a Translation of Al'Kabor!<br><br>transcript of Translation of Al'Kabor<br><br>.... then I took the bricks which I had found and enscribed them with the spells which I entrusted to my order.  The secrets to making these bricks and the portal spells I have entrusted to my order, only with enough of these may the portals be opened....<br><br>You say, "What portal spells?"<br>Al'trar the sorcerer says, "Ah so you wish to engrave the magic bricks, here, have these spell patterns."<br>You receive a stack of 20 portal spell rune patterns.<br><br>You say, "How do I create the bricks?"<br>Al'trar the sorcerer says, "You must collect a pure block of steel, a block of fire essence, a block of sand of the south,  a block of the power of Luclin."<br>--pure block of steel = 2 High quality large brick + 1 water = 1 high quality block of ore<br>-- a block of fire essence = 2 large brick of condensed flame + 1 water = 1 block of condensed flame<br>-- a block of sand of the south = (Pottery 180) + 3 "sands of the field (found in field of bones)" + 1 water + 1 "vial of binding" (bought in Cabalis) = 1 clay brick, 2 clay brick + 1 "vial of binding" (must be fired with hq firing sheet 190) = 1 block of hardened sands<br>-- a block of the power of Luclin = 2 large bricks of acrylia + 1 water = 1 block of acrylia<br>-- All four blocks combines by a smith (250) = 1 dull magic brick<br>-- Combined by wizard with research skill 1 dull magic brick + 1 portal spell rune pattern = 1 portal brick<br><br>(You give 1 portal brick to Al'Kabor's Taskmaster)<br>Al'Kabor's Taskmaster says, "Thank you! We have far to go, but our order grows every day!"<br>Your party gains experience!<br><br>Every time the taskmaster receives a brick it is noted in a log.  When, say 10k bricks have been turned in, a GM would bring the zone down, swap it to a version of the zone with the spires in it, and bring the zone back up.  You would have to patch your zone file before you could reenter that zone.<br><br>Instead of Al'Kabor's Taskmaster, A member of Al'Kabor's order would spawn.  He is a merchant, and sells the spells: Portal to:ZONE and Gate:ZONE.  These are level 49 and 39 wizard spells. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uzlatershadowprowler.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zlater ShadowProwler</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/4/02 11:34:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23171.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Moneysinks and Epic Cooperative Quests</span><hr size=1> Its an industrious idea. I'd like to see a server actually build something that benefits everyone in particular rather than one small group. Would people put in the time for something they couldnt wear or cast tho... that is hard to say!<br><br>Also my lore is a bit sketchy, but I think it was the Combine empire that put all the portals in place. Since that empire is long gone, I dont think we would have the knowledge to recreate the portals. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=